Docs.summary: The Gateway agent pool associates one public IPPrefix for each static egress gateway to provide public egress. The size of Public IPPrefix should be selected by the user. Each node in the agent pool is assigned with one IP from the IPPrefix. The IPPrefix size thus serves as a cap on the size of the Gateway agent pool. Due to Azure public IPPrefix size limitation, the valid value range is [28, 31] (/31 = 2 nodes/IPs, /30 = 4 nodes/IPs, /29 = 8 nodes/IPs, /28 = 16 nodes/IPs). The default value is 31. Serialized Name: AgentPoolGatewayProfile.publicIPPrefixSize

MemberSignature.Value: member this.OrchestratorVersion : string with get, set

Docs.summary: The version of Kubernetes specified by the user. Both patch version <major.minor.patch> (e.g. 1.20.13) and <major.minor> (e.g. 1.20) are supported. When <major.minor> is specified, the latest supported GA patch version is chosen automatically. Updating the cluster with the same <major.minor> once it has been created (e.g. 1.14.x -> 1.14) will not trigger an upgrade, even if a newer patch version is available. As a best practice, you should upgrade all node pools in an AKS cluster to the same Kubernetes version. The node pool version must have the same major version as the control plane. The node pool minor version must be within two minor versions of the control plane version. The node pool version cannot be greater than the control plane version. For more information see [upgrading a node pool](https://docs.microsoft.com/azure/aks/use-multiple-node-pools#upgrade-a-node-pool). Serialized Name: AgentPool.properties.orchestratorVersion
